...Advices Nigerians to Avoid Travelling to High Burden Countries The Presidential Task Force (PTF) on COVID-19 has warned that voters without facemasks would not be allowed to perform their civic responsibility during Ondo governorship election on Saturday October 10th.  National Coordinator of the PTF, Dr Sani Aliyu, who disclosed this during the Task force press briefing in Abuja, also revealed that new guidelines have been released for safe reopening of schools and to minimize transmission of the virus across the country.  Our correspondent Nathan Williams reports that the Secretary to the Government of the Federation and Chairman of the PTF on Covid-19 Mr Boss Mustapha said though the recovery rate is high, it is imperative for everyone to get tested however decried lack of trust in government agencies by citizens.  The Minister of Health Dr. Osagie Ehanire during the briefing also noted that Nigerians should avoid non-essential travels to high burden countries to avoid importing the virus into the country thereby leading to further spread.